what does this command do: ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com
This is a SSH command that allows you to connect to an EC2 instance (user) on the Amazon Web Services cloud using your private key file (~/UserKey.pem). The -i option specifies the path of your private key, and "-C" enables compression for faster transfer speeds. Additionally, "L 259:0:localhost:590 0:" sets up a local port forwarding to forward traffic from port 590 on the EC2 instance (user) to ports 5900-5910 in your home network. This command can be used with various SSH clients such as PuTTY or OpenSSH.
